HEADWORD: Whether
<hw>Wheth"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>whether</ets>, AS. <ets>hw⟦ae⟧<?/er</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>hwe<?/ar</ets>, OFries. <ets>hweder</ets>, OHG. <ets>hwedar</ets>,
<ets>wedar</ets>, G. <ets>weder</ets>, conj., neither, Icel.
<ets>hv⟦amac⟧rr</ets> whether, Goth. <ets>hwa<?/ar</ets>, Lith.
<ets>katras</ets>, L. <ets>uter</ets>, Gr. <?/, <?/, Skr.
<ets>katara</ets>, from the interrogatively pronoun, in AS.
<ets>hw⟦amac⟧</ets> who. <?/<?/<?/<?/. See <er>Who</er>, and cf.
<er>Either</er>, <er>Neither</er>, <er>Or</er>, <ets>conj</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Which (of two); which one (of two); -- used interrogatively and
relatively.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now choose yourself <qex>whether</qex> that you liketh.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One day in doubt I cast for to compare⟦br⟧
<qex>Whether</qex> in beauties' glory did exceed.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whether</qex> of them twain did the will of his father?</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xxi. 31.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whether</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whether
<hw>Wheth"er</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>In case; if; -- used to
introduce the first or two or more alternative clauses, the other or
others being connected by <xex>or</xex>, or by <xex>or whether</xex>.
When the second of two alternatives is the simple negative of the first
it is sometimes only indicated by the particle <xex>not</xex> or
<xex>no</xex> after the correlative, and sometimes it is omitted
entirely as being distinctly implied in the <xex>whether</xex> of the
first.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And now who knows⟦br⟧
But you, Lorenzo, <qex>whether</qex> I am yours?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have said; but <qex>whether</qex> wisely or no, let the forest
judge.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For <qex>whether</qex> we live, we live unto the Lord; and
<qex>whether</qex> we die, we die unto the Lord; <qex>whether</qex> we
live therefore, or die, we are the Lord's.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. xiv.
8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But <qex>whether</qex> thus these things, or <qex>whether</qex>
not;⟦br⟧
<qex>Whether</qex> the sun, predominant in heaven,⟦br⟧
Rise on the earth, or earth rise on the sun, . . . ⟦br⟧
Solicit not thy thoughts with matters hid.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Whether or no</b></col>, <cd>in either case; in any case;
as, I will go <xex>whether or no</xex>.</cd> -- <col><b>Whether
that</b></col>, <cd>whether.</cd> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whethering</ent>⟦br⟧
